him, Naarada then
समम्-अङ्गिरसा
along with Angirasa
दयालु:
merciful (Naarada)
सम्प्राप्य
approaching
तावत्-उपदर्श्य
then showed
सुतस्य जीवम्
the son's soul
कस्य-अस्मि पुत्र(:) इति
whose son am I, thus
तस्य गिरा
by his speech
विमोहं त्यक्त्वा
giving up delusion
त्वत्-अर्चन-विधौ
in the ways of Thy worship
नृपतिं न्ययुङ्क्त
gave instructions to the king

s16
00:03:30.833 --> 00:03:52.000 align:start
The merciful Naarada and sage Angirasa went to Chitraketu and showed him the soul of his dead son. The soul asked 'whose son am I?' These words dispelled the king's delusion. The sages then instructed him in the ways of Thy worship.
---------
